waddington.kai.main.knnf.serialisation

Class NetworkLoader

  • java.lang.Object
    • waddington.kai.main.knnf.serialisation.NetworkLoader

  • public class NetworkLoader
extends java.lang.Object
    This class handles loading a previously created neural network model that was created by this package. The model file should be placed in the appropriate location and the model name should be provided. The model file is a .zip file containing a directory for the model. Inside this directory is a .json file containing information about the NetworkManager, as well as this, there is a directory for each layer. Inside the layer directories is a .json file containing information for that layer, as well as this there is a directory for the neurons in that layer. Inside this directory there is a .json file for each neuron.

      • getLayers

        private static NetworkManager getLayers(java.lang.String pRoot,
                                        java.lang.String tempDir,
                                        java.lang.String fileName,
                                        NetworkManager network)
                                 throws java.io.FileNotFoundException,
                                        java.io.IOException,
                                        org.json.simple.parser.ParseException
        Loads the layers of the model. Each layer is stored in it's own directory which also contains the neuron files as well. The method used to get the number of layers is from stackoverflow: - https://stackoverflow.com/a/18300155/3259361
        Parameters:
        pRoot - A locally set path to the root of the project.
        tempDir - The name of the temporary directory.
        fileName - The name of the model file, without extension.
        network - The instance of NetworkManager.
        Returns:
        The instance of NetworkManager with the layers added.
        Throws:
        java.io.FileNotFoundException - If a layer file cannot be read.
        java.io.IOException - If a layer file cannot be found.
        org.json.simple.parser.ParseException - If the json data cannot be parsed.

      • loadManager

        private static NetworkManager loadManager(java.lang.String pRoot,
                                          java.lang.String tempDir,
                                          java.lang.String fileName,
                                          NetworkManager network)
                                   throws java.io.FileNotFoundException,
                                          java.io.IOException,
                                          org.json.simple.parser.ParseException
        Loads the settings of the NetworkManager instance. The settings are saved in a "NetworkManager.json" file.
        Parameters:
        pRoot - A locally set path to the root of the project.
        tempDir - The name of the temporary directory.
        fileName - The name of the model file, without extension.
        network - The instance of NetworkManager.
        Returns:
        The instance of NetworkManager with hyper-parameters set.
        Throws:
        java.io.FileNotFoundException - If cannot find the file.
        java.io.IOException - If cannot read the file.
        org.json.simple.parser.ParseException - If the json cannot be parsed.

      • unpackNetwork

        private static void unpackNetwork(java.lang.String pathToRoot,
                                  java.lang.String tempDirName,
                                  java.lang.String saveDirName,
                                  java.lang.String fileName)
                           throws java.lang.Exception
        The model files are a .zip file, this method unpacks the .zip to the temporary directory created by createTempFileStructure(String, String).
        Parameters:
        pathToRoot - A locally set path to the root of the project.
        tempDirName - The name of the temporary directory.
        saveDirName - The name of the directory where the model file is placed.
        fileName - The name of the model file, without extension.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - When the model file cannot be read or when the model file cannot be unpacked.
